Subject: [bioinfo] Bioinformaticien a Chypre

Vacancy for Bioinformatician

NIPD Genetics LTD is a privately held start-up company aiming to
commercially exploit the recent discovery
of the Cyprus Institute of Neurology and Genetics for Non-Invasive
Prenatal Diagnosis of Down Syndrome.

THE POSITION
We seek to recruit a Bioinformatician to join our dynamic team of scientists.

(Reference Code: NIPD04)
MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS
PhD degree in Bioinformatics or closely related fields
Candidates must have strong computational and statistical analysis
skills, and be proficient with Unix/Linux command line environments,
database design such as SQL, as well as one or more of the following
programming languages; C, C++, Perl, Python, Java or R.

The following qualifications will be considered an advantage
Familiarity with the Unix/Linux operating systems
Prior experience with next generation sequencing data analysis
Knowledge of genome assembly and large-scale data mining
Familiarity with NGS sample preparation methodologies and
high-throughput sequencing
Experience in parallel programming
Experience in molecular biology and genetics
Good communication skills

To apply please forward a detailed curriculum vitae together with
names of two referees and a cover letter to NIPD Genetics Ltd by the
17th January 2014 at the following address: Personnel Office, NIPD
Genetics Ltd P.O.Box 27954, Engomi, CY-2434 Nicosia, or by e-mail at:
c.anastassiades@nipd.com  stating the reference code.
For further information please contact:Costas Anastassiades, tel.:
22266888 e-mail: c.anastassiades@nipd.com; www.nipd.com.

